The paper deals with the store languages of language acceptors, which is a topic in formal language theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various data structures used in language acceptors, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of store languages involves analyzing the space complexity of language acceptors, which is related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses connections between different types of language acceptors, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper presents a technique for proving closure properties of families of languages, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
